<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Scarpa</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-06 18:40:08</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Clerics can't solo Grimrot because his MAGIC resist is very high (I've heard 95)<BR>
<BR>
The trick is use fire based or cold based spells, or melee.  Even though a 50 cleric can't solo him, a 40 cleric and a 35 warrior could do it easily.  A druid and a cleric could do it easily.  etc...<BR>
<BR>
I've seen 2 live Grimrots, but not dead Grimrot.  Is there a trick to making 1 spawn over the other?  The other thing I noticed is that the Putrid Skeletons are NOT placeholders.  He spawns in a unique spot.  Can anyone confirm or deny this?</font></td></tr></table>
