<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Prexus Cleric</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-11 13:08:57</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>To answer some questions, if you give the fish corpses to the wandering paladin that wanders around the temple of life. You will see him if you just look around. He doesnt go very far.<BR>
Next you cant even get the quest unless you have medium warmly and you must have maxed faction with the temple to complete. Amiably will not work. You always get the shield if you have maxed faction and turn in the right items<BR>
Yes, the shield can be worn on the back, so dont get rid of your charred guardian shield. )<BR>
To make Grimrot spawn, just kill the putrid skellies, they will give you faction and he will spawn. Both grimrots use the same spawn spot. The undead is not magic resistant. He dies easily. <BR>
To kill the Live grimrot, just have a mid to high 30's tank and a cleric to heal. A 37 warrior killed the live with only 2 superior heals.<BR>
I hope this helps. Good Luck.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
