<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Laetorn</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-11 22:22:09</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, I just received my Aegis (finally). Ever since i handed in the items a few weeks ago, and did not receive it, i have been working on faction. (Camlend did give me the quest then, but I didnt have maximum warmly faction) The only quests I have been doing were fighting putrids, donating (less than 200pp in all), and bone chips (only around 200). I never did any other quests (oil, sashes, etc.) When I went to try to hand in the items again today, putrids still gave me faction when i hit them. This tells me that you DO NOT need maximum faction anymore. I believe that this quest may have been fixed in the recent patch. Camlend now bows to me when I hail him. This may be a sign that you have enough faction, but I cant be sure. Well, all I am saying is that you don't need max faction so dont go overboard. Oh yeah, along with the Aegis, I got a bubble of exp and level 30 for handing in the items, a nice little bonus :) Good luck all</font></td></tr></table>
