<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: </font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-21 14:49:56</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok to answer some questions. <BR>
I have the Aegis of Life and it may have a Shield icon but you will not find the word Shield associated with it.<BR>
1. It fits in the back slot and for my money is the best non-planes cloak around.<BR>
2. Requirements, you need the No-Drop scythe and the No-Drop heart. I have seen both drop off the same Grimrot! rare but has happened.<BR>
3. Faction requirement is still Warmly, after patch it does not have to be maxed but does reqiured fairly high faction, so you may want to go a little overboard just for safety sake.<BR>
4. *BEWARE* Grimrot in human form has been known to spawn in MILTIPLES yes you heard me Multiples..as in more than one 35-38 Shadow knight at once..nasty very nasty. I have seen this 3 times myself and it aint pretty.<BR>
5. Killing him in undead form is fairly easy and if your a solo Paladin anywhere over 40 you should have no problem and if your a cleric 35 or above should be ok due to your undead spells.<BR>
6. Live Shadow knight version, appears to be about 35-38th level and has all the abilities that i have come to hate..Harm Touch ! and remember note 3. !! anyhow I have succesfuly killed him with a 45th pal and 34th cleric team. however if there is a multiple spawn...RUN !!<BR>
7. Faction quests I have soulfire and that required faction also, my faction upon starting the quest was kindly, I used the following to get my faction to Warmly. 20 bandit sashes, 24 rabid pelts, ~150 putrid skeleton kills, 500 bone chips (ick) and 250 gp.<BR>
8. there are many posts here about the faction quests so I wont go over them you should be able to find all you need on almost any EQ website.<BR>
9. Spawn time. seems everyone has different opinions on this, i have seen it take ours to minutes to get respawn so just except the need to camp and bring some friends to talk with =)<BR>
Final comment, to use this as a shield is a waste..hehe..just my opinion. If you have any questions and are on the Bristlebane server send a tell to.. Tyrusstorm<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
